
[1]thou

   THOU, pron. in the obj. thee. The second personal pronoun, in the
   singular number; the pronoun which is used in addressing persons in the
   solemn style.

   Art thou he that should come? Matt.11.

   I will fear no evil, for thou art with me. Ps.23.

       Thou is used only in the solemn style, unless in very familiar
                        language, and by the Quakers.

                    THOU, v.t. To treat with familiarity.

   If thou thouest him some thrice, it shall not be amiss.

                THOU, v.i. To use thou and thee in discourse.
